em.passagen.se/trench/sr/icon1.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle><font color=#FFFF66>Board Administrator</font></span><br>  Posts: 1528<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(1/3/02 1:42:21 pm)</font><br>    </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Shamans</span><hr size=1> Ogres: Can't be stunned from the front, infravision, Ivandyr's hoop, slam.<br>
Trolls: Regen, infravision, Ivandyr's hoop, slam.<br>
Barbs: Can wear some medium armor, slam.<br>
Iksar: Can't wear plate, ultravision, regen, no slam.<br>
Vah'Shir: Infravision, no slam.<br>
<br>
It all depends what level you are aiming for.<br>
If you aim for an endgame character, then I'd suggest troll or Ogre.<br>
If you aim for a low level ( &lt;level 40), then I suggest Barbarian or Iksar.<br>
<br>
Iksar has a big disadvantage in not being able to use the Jaundiced Bone Bracer, which basicly is our only way to solo and do damage to bigger encounters in the endgame.<br>
Regeneration is a very nice ability, coupled up with cannabalize it is an indirect form of manaregeneration.<br>
Barbarians lack the vision, and in the endgame faction doesn't matter. There are a few armors that barbarians can wear that the large races can't, but those stopped dropping in Kunark, more or less. The only item that actually matters now is the shoulders from the hole, which many replaceable same or better quality shoulders in the endgame.<br>
<br>
The choice is really between Ogre and Troll, Not being able to get stunned can save your life, while the regen will make you more efficient, cause you will get mana faster. Trolls also can get the symbol of innoruuk, which makes them the only shaman race able to snare their target, which is a huge help when soloing, or in group without wiz/ranger/druid/necro/sk (well, it can happend!).<br>
<br>
my personal order for best-&gt;worst shaman class would be:<br>
1. Troll<br>
2. Ogre<br>
3. Barbarian<br>
4. Iksar<br>
<br>
don't know enough about the Vah'Shiir yet to know what equip they can wear and how good shamans they can be. <p><a href=http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=21834 target=_document >
